   Evening sun behind the drill dome at the
   GISP2 site in central Greenland.

   Sponsored by the National Science Foundation, teams of scientists and
   drillers travel to the ice sheets and glaciers of the world to recover
   ice cores which will yield information on past climate states of the
   earth.

